From Wiktionary, the free dictionary
See also: auto, autó, aùto, autō, aŭto, auto-, Auto., and Appendix:Variations of "auto"

English

[edit]

Proper noun

[edit]

Auto

  1. An unincorporated community in West Virginia.

Anagrams

[edit]
  • aout, outa

Bavarian

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From French automobile.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ˈɑɔ̯d̥ːo/
  • IPA(key): /ˈɒːd̥ːo/ (Vienna)

Noun

[edit]

Auto n (plural Auto)

  1. car

German

[edit]
German Wikipedia has an article on:
Auto
Wikipedia de

Etymology

[edit]

    Clipping of Automobil, from French automobile.

    Pronunciation

    [edit]
    • IPA(key): /ˈaʊ̯to/, [ˈʔaʊ̯tʰoˑ]
    • Audio:(file)
    • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)
    • Audio (Germany (Berlin), voice of a child):(file)
    • Audio (Austria):(file)
    • Hyphenation: Au‧to

    Noun

    [edit]

    Auto n (strong, genitive Autos, plural Autos)

    1. car
      Synonyms: (jocular) Benzinkutsche, (informal) Karre, (informal) Kiste, (officialese) KFZ, Wagen
      Das ist das Auto meines Vaters.
      That is my father’s car.

    Declension

    [edit]
    Declension of Auto [neuter, strong]
    singular plural
    indef. def. noun def. noun
    nominative ein das Auto die Autos
    genitive eines des Autos der Autos
    dative einem dem Auto den Autos
    accusative ein das Auto die Autos

    Hunsrik

    [edit]

    Alternative forms

    [edit]
    • auto (Wiesemann spelling)

    Etymology

    [edit]
    Etymology tree
    Ancient Greek αὐτός (autós)
    Ancient Greek αὐτο- (auto-)lbor.
    French auto-
    Proto-Indo-European *m(y)ewh₁-der.
    Proto-Italic *moweō
    Latin moveō
    Latin -bilis
    Latin mōbilislbor.
    French mobile
    French automobilebor.
    German Automobil
    German Autobor.
    Hunsrik Auto

      Borrowed from German Auto.[1]

      Pronunciation

      [edit]
      • IPA(key): /ˈaʊ̯to/
      • Rhymes: -aʊ̯to
      • Syllabification: Au‧to

      Noun

      [edit]

      Auto n (plural Autos)

      1. car; automobile
        Synonym: Karre
        Er hod en neies Auto kaafd.
        He bought a new car.

      References

      [edit]
